1
00:00:02,580 --> 00:00:06,480
Next is the continuation of
our report on the UMAs,

2
00:00:06,480 --> 00:00:09,230
or Unidentified Mysterious Animals,
that have recently been sighted.

3
00:00:09,890 --> 00:00:15,340
The difference between this and our previous
report is the increasing number of victims,

4
00:00:15,340 --> 00:00:19,410
and the amount of evidence supporting
the existence of these creatures.

5
00:00:19,740 --> 00:00:23,790
In any case, many of the witnesses are
active members of the police force.

6
00:00:23,790 --> 00:00:26,070
And over half of the officers

7
00:00:26,070 --> 00:00:30,550
who have rushed to the scenes have
been killed by these creatures.

8
00:00:30,980 --> 00:00:34,920
These are images of unidentified creatures
that have been attacking the police.

9
00:00:35,510 --> 00:00:40,010
You can see the victims on the
ground at the creatures' feet.

10
00:00:41,390 --> 00:00:45,810
What we know is that all these creatures
are violent, capable of speech,

11
00:00:45,810 --> 00:00:48,810
and show no fear of humans.

12
00:00:49,360 --> 00:00:52,700
A prime example is this interview
with the lion man of Nevaska.

13
00:00:53,140 --> 00:00:56,950
He spoke at length of a crude theory
about the existence of a kingdom.

14
00:00:57,700 --> 00:01:02,480
The woman interviewing him listened
patiently to what he had to say,

15
00:01:02,480 --> 00:01:06,960
but eventually, she asked the
question on every viewer's mind.

16
00:01:07,820 --> 00:01:11,630
Can you prove that you
truly are what you claim?

17
00:01:12,920 --> 00:01:16,030
Those were her last words.

18
00:01:20,400 --> 00:01:22,570
So far, the unidentified creatures

19
00:01:22,570 --> 00:01:26,120
have only appeared on the Yorbian continent.

20
00:01:26,120 --> 00:01:28,910
But it seems likely that they
will continue to spread,

21
00:01:28,910 --> 00:01:33,150
and no effective method of dealing
with them has been found.

22
00:01:33,560 --> 00:01:34,740
Sorry for the wait.

23
00:01:36,730 --> 00:01:38,990
Okay, let's go.

24
00:02:59,030 --> 00:03:04,030
A x Lawless x Home

25
00:03:09,080 --> 00:03:11,570
They're known as Chimera Ants.

26
00:03:11,960 --> 00:03:13,260
I know.

27
00:03:13,260 --> 00:03:15,170
They became that way after mixing with humans.

28
00:03:15,630 --> 00:03:20,110
Working backwards from the dates and
locations of sightings and police reports,

29
00:03:20,110 --> 00:03:22,580
they probably originated in the Balsa Islands.

30
00:03:22,580 --> 00:03:25,680
Lots of strange nations are in that area.

31
00:03:25,970 --> 00:03:28,560
You shouldn't be talking about
how strange other people are.

32
00:03:28,870 --> 00:03:31,200
But they were once ants...

33
00:03:31,200 --> 00:03:34,060
So they should just stay close to their nest.

34
00:03:34,570 --> 00:03:37,430
Why come all the way out here?

35
00:03:37,830 --> 00:03:38,990
No idea.

36
00:03:38,990 --> 00:03:42,660
Maybe they were just wandering, or perhaps
they were drawn to the smell of garbage.

37
00:03:42,660 --> 00:03:44,570
It can't be a coincidence.

38
00:03:44,960 --> 00:03:48,260
Both NGL and East Gorteau are nations

39
00:03:48,260 --> 00:03:50,870
that share no information with the outside world.

40
00:03:51,230 --> 00:03:53,970
Just like this place.

41
00:03:53,970 --> 00:03:58,340
That makes it easier for them to invade.

42
00:04:04,660 --> 00:04:06,350
It's been quite a long time.

43
00:04:07,120 --> 00:04:09,350
The place hasn't changed...

44
00:04:18,720 --> 00:04:20,110
What's the situation?

45
00:04:20,970 --> 00:04:25,730
Between the victims and martyrs,
we're seeing over three hundred dead.

46
00:04:26,250 --> 00:04:30,120
Bombs have no effect, so we can't fight back.

47
00:04:32,450 --> 00:04:36,980
The council is still arguing about
how to classify the dead.

48
00:04:37,550 --> 00:04:39,130
What do you mean?

49
00:04:45,650 --> 00:04:48,760
A few days ago, this was an ordinary human.

50
00:04:48,760 --> 00:04:50,710
The Ants did this?

51
00:04:50,710 --> 00:04:53,020
Looks dead to me.

52
00:04:53,440 --> 00:04:55,140
What's the problem?

53
00:04:56,410 --> 00:04:59,650
Some are alive and working with the Ants.

54
00:05:00,340 --> 00:05:02,690
And all of them look like monsters.

55
00:05:03,690 --> 00:05:06,910
The council's debate is whether
to declare them dead based on

56
00:05:06,910 --> 00:05:12,240
whether or not there's a way to
restore them to their original forms.

57
00:05:13,710 --> 00:05:15,620
They can't avenge them because

58
00:05:15,620 --> 00:05:19,810
they're too busy arguing over
whether they're dead or mutated?

59
00:05:26,260 --> 00:05:28,610
Nothing's changed.

60
00:05:28,610 --> 00:05:31,100
They always lose sight of what's important.

61
00:05:31,980 --> 00:05:34,080
We're going to do things our way.

62
00:05:34,870 --> 00:05:37,560
If anyone interferes, we'll take them down.

63
00:05:38,610 --> 00:05:39,960
Don't worry.

64
00:05:41,290 --> 00:05:43,730
Before the day is out,

65
00:05:44,710 --> 00:05:46,800
we'll exterminate this so-called Queen.

66
00:05:49,970 --> 00:05:52,080
I am the Queen.

67
00:05:52,780 --> 00:05:54,080
I repeat.

68
00:05:54,600 --> 00:05:56,080
Surrender.

69
00:05:56,870 --> 00:05:59,760
Those who resist will be executed.

70
00:06:00,220 --> 00:06:04,850
The chosen will live in paradise for eternity!

71
00:06:08,110 --> 00:06:10,480
Our mother's greatest flaw

72
00:06:10,480 --> 00:06:14,140
was that she could only produce soldiers

73
00:06:14,140 --> 00:06:16,630
through the archaic and inefficient laying of eggs.

74
00:06:17,370 --> 00:06:19,600
Her sole achievement

75
00:06:21,280 --> 00:06:23,330
was giving birth to me.

76
00:06:24,760 --> 00:06:25,760
Stop...

77
00:06:26,170 --> 00:06:27,190
Kill me!

78
00:06:27,660 --> 00:06:29,110
Kill me!

79
00:06:30,010 --> 00:06:31,870
Plenty of spirit...

80
00:06:32,620 --> 00:06:33,910
He shows promise.

81
00:06:52,610 --> 00:06:53,550
Bingo.

82
00:06:53,980 --> 00:06:56,940
Chosen one, welcome to paradise.

83
00:06:57,750 --> 00:07:01,310
Swear eternal fealty to the Queen.

84
00:07:03,740 --> 00:07:06,070
I am the Queen.

85
00:07:06,170 --> 00:07:13,070
Sexy Stinger of Rebirth

86
00:07:08,490 --> 00:07:11,740
With my Queen Shot, I shall control the world.

87
00:07:14,500 --> 00:07:16,080
Let's go through the front door.

88
00:07:16,920 --> 00:07:18,860
No objection here...

89
00:07:24,540 --> 00:07:26,090
No one's around.

90
00:07:26,810 --> 00:07:29,480
Are they inviting us in?

91
00:07:30,010 --> 00:07:31,840
Then I'll go this way.

92
00:07:32,280 --> 00:07:33,960
I'll take this way.

93
00:07:34,710 --> 00:07:36,040
We're splitting up?

94
00:07:36,040 --> 00:07:39,600
Of course... It's a race to see
who'll kill the Queen.

95
00:07:40,030 --> 00:07:43,920
I imagine you'd prefer to hide
your abilities from us.

96
00:07:44,320 --> 00:07:47,150
Kill anything that attacks you.

97
00:07:47,150 --> 00:07:51,240
If you kill the Queen, you're the interim boss.

98
00:07:51,980 --> 00:07:52,910
Understood.

99
00:07:53,840 --> 00:07:54,740
Start!

100
00:07:58,210 --> 00:07:59,750
They've scattered.

101
00:08:00,290 --> 00:08:07,640
From their footsteps, I can sense
that these intruders are special.

102
00:08:07,640 --> 00:08:11,010
They are accustomed to living in the wild.

103
00:08:11,800 --> 00:08:13,160
Are they strong?

104
00:08:13,160 --> 00:08:14,290
Yes.

105
00:08:15,460 --> 00:08:17,640
Then go and greet them.

106
00:08:17,640 --> 00:08:22,550
But then, no one will be here to guard you.

107
00:08:22,550 --> 00:08:24,420
If you're worried about me,

108
00:08:24,420 --> 00:08:27,940
capture the enemy and hurry back.

109
00:08:29,210 --> 00:08:31,570
I have faith in you, Pike.

110
00:08:32,710 --> 00:08:36,410
Y-You are too kind...

111
00:08:36,410 --> 00:08:40,240
I will serve you with my life!

112
00:08:41,320 --> 00:08:43,320
Off I go!

113
00:08:45,280 --> 00:08:47,080
Now, then...

114
00:08:48,170 --> 00:08:49,590
You're heading out?

115
00:08:51,630 --> 00:08:54,140
My mother's greatest misfortune

116
00:08:54,140 --> 00:08:57,500
was that she never experienced
the joy of combat.

117
00:09:10,600 --> 00:09:12,360
You're no fun...

118
00:09:13,520 --> 00:09:15,240
Let me hold you.

119
00:09:15,540 --> 00:09:17,800
I'll send you to heaven.

120
00:09:26,340 --> 00:09:27,530
Moles.

121
00:09:27,530 --> 00:09:29,750
No, holes?

122
00:09:48,270 --> 00:09:53,310
Bonolenov descended from a small tribe
that industrialization had driven out of

123
00:09:53,310 --> 00:09:55,720
its ancestral lands, the Gyudondond.

124
00:09:56,270 --> 00:10:00,800
When Gyudondond males reach the age of three,

125
00:10:00,800 --> 00:10:03,780
needles are used to puncture holes in their body.

126
00:10:03,780 --> 00:10:07,030
Depending on the holes' size and shape,

127
00:10:07,030 --> 00:10:10,320
and the movements the Gyudondond
make, they can produce sound.

128
00:10:10,870 --> 00:10:14,100
Before fighting rival tribes or wild animals,

129
00:10:14,100 --> 00:10:18,470
they would play a battle song using
their own bodies as instruments.

130
00:10:18,840 --> 00:10:21,880
They are known as the Bapu, dancing warriors.

131
00:10:20,760 --> 00:10:24,590
Bapu
Dancing Warriors

132
00:10:22,310 --> 00:10:24,680
They believe the more beautiful

133
00:10:24,680 --> 00:10:28,040
the sound produced, the stronger
the spirit that descends.

134
00:10:28,040 --> 00:10:31,510
The most skilled Bapu are treated as gods,

135
00:10:31,510 --> 00:10:34,230
and hold more influence than the elders.

136
00:10:37,480 --> 00:10:40,390
Transform this melody into strength to fight!

137
00:10:37,550 --> 00:10:41,560
Battle Cantabile

138
00:10:40,390 --> 00:10:42,260
Battle Cantabile...

139
00:10:42,950 --> 00:10:44,200
Prologue

140
00:10:43,080 --> 00:10:44,200
Prologue!

141
00:10:53,590 --> 00:10:55,520
The blood of my tribe,

142
00:10:55,520 --> 00:10:58,440
the most beautiful in battle,
flows through my veins.

143
00:10:58,910 --> 00:11:01,720
I swear on the names of the spirits and my tribe

144
00:11:01,720 --> 00:11:04,200
that you will not best me.

145
00:11:05,400 --> 00:11:10,990
Was that attack supposed
to hold your tribe's pride?

146
00:11:10,990 --> 00:11:12,230
If so...

147
00:11:14,080 --> 00:11:16,860
You must not feel much pride.

148
00:11:19,000 --> 00:11:21,370
Don't bother recanting those words.

149
00:11:21,370 --> 00:11:23,730
They are but a beast's ramblings.

150
00:11:24,180 --> 00:11:26,500
They cannot affect me!

151
00:11:29,180 --> 00:11:32,850
In a one-on-one fight, my opponent's
strength doesn't matter.

152
00:11:32,850 --> 00:11:35,450
If I can pierce it with this, I'll win.

153
00:11:35,450 --> 00:11:37,510
But I'm not certain I can pierce that...

154
00:11:43,560 --> 00:11:45,930
Those are sharp...

155
00:11:45,930 --> 00:11:47,610
I'll need to slip in between them

156
00:11:47,610 --> 00:11:52,270
and insert the antenna into the joint
exposed when he moves the arm.

157
00:11:52,810 --> 00:11:54,770
Chance of succeeding unscathed...

158
00:11:55,380 --> 00:11:56,770
Twenty percent!

159
00:12:09,860 --> 00:12:11,340
Okay, it worked...

160
00:12:11,880 --> 00:12:12,750
Ow.

161
00:12:13,480 --> 00:12:15,580
Guess escaping unharmed wasn't possible.

162
00:12:19,320 --> 00:12:20,090
Huh?

163
00:12:20,900 --> 00:12:23,250
Why didn't it work?

164
00:12:23,250 --> 00:12:25,810
I put the antenna in...

165
00:12:25,810 --> 00:12:27,850
You must be a Manipulator.

166
00:12:28,500 --> 00:12:32,650
I can tell because, once you placed
that antenna in Pell, you relaxed.

167
00:12:33,210 --> 00:12:36,670
That must be the condition
for activating your power.

168
00:12:36,670 --> 00:12:39,530
You let your guard down
when you thought it worked.

169
00:12:40,440 --> 00:12:42,380
Its name is Pell?

170
00:12:42,940 --> 00:12:44,530
You must also be a Manipulator.

171
00:12:45,700 --> 00:12:49,360
If my power doesn't activate after
the condition has been met,

172
00:12:49,360 --> 00:12:52,790
that means my target is already being
manipulated by another Nen user.

173
00:12:53,280 --> 00:12:55,540
That, and he has a remote controller.

174
00:12:55,870 --> 00:12:57,970
Oh, you knew?

175
00:12:57,970 --> 00:13:01,050
Yes, it's first come, first served for Manipulators.

176
00:13:01,370 --> 00:13:06,300
Once I take you to the Queen, my job is done.

177
00:13:08,260 --> 00:13:09,050
No good...

178
00:13:09,470 --> 00:13:11,200
I can't break free.

179
00:13:12,200 --> 00:13:13,850
Guess there's no choice.

180
00:13:14,260 --> 00:13:16,860
I'd rather not have to use this...

181
00:13:20,800 --> 00:13:23,570
Your punch stings about as
much as a mosquito bite.

182
00:13:24,190 --> 00:13:25,700
What's next?

183
00:13:25,700 --> 00:13:26,820
You gonna kick me?

184
00:13:26,820 --> 00:13:27,570
Pull out a weapon?

185
00:13:28,360 --> 00:13:32,080
As a gift to you on your way to the afterlife,
I'll grant you one more attack.

186
00:13:32,480 --> 00:13:35,720
For an ant, you know some big words.

187
00:13:36,130 --> 00:13:38,230
Then I'll take you up on that...

188
00:13:38,700 --> 00:13:40,000
And go with a punch.

189
00:13:41,240 --> 00:13:43,260
You're sure? Really?

190
00:13:43,870 --> 00:13:45,920
Fifteen should do it.

191
00:13:46,400 --> 00:13:47,750
Fifteen?

192
00:13:48,770 --> 00:13:52,780
Four, five, six...

193
00:13:56,380 --> 00:14:01,440
Eleven, twelve, thirteen, fourteen...

194
00:14:02,080 --> 00:14:03,700
Fifteen!

195
00:14:06,630 --> 00:14:07,700
Huh?

196
00:14:08,660 --> 00:14:11,200
I get a free attack, right?

197
00:14:11,620 --> 00:14:13,450
W-Wait!

198
00:14:17,980 --> 00:14:24,460
Karmic Loop

199
00:14:18,560 --> 00:14:22,460
Every time I wind my arm, my punch gets stronger.

200
00:14:22,460 --> 00:14:24,960
Ripper Cyclotron!

201
00:14:22,710 --> 00:14:24,460
Ripper Cyclotron

202
00:14:31,090 --> 00:14:35,180
Oh, half of that would have been enough.

203
00:14:35,180 --> 00:14:38,450
I never seem to know how much power to use.

204
00:14:38,450 --> 00:14:39,480
Now, then...

205
00:14:40,000 --> 00:14:41,800
Which way to go?

206
00:14:42,700 --> 00:14:44,160
Right?

207
00:14:44,940 --> 00:14:46,570
Or left?

208
00:14:48,260 --> 00:14:50,280
I'll flip a coin.

209
00:14:59,240 --> 00:15:02,000
What's going to happen to me?

210
00:15:02,000 --> 00:15:03,840
You'll become a slave.

211
00:15:03,840 --> 00:15:06,800
You'll work for the Queen until you die.

212
00:15:06,800 --> 00:15:09,760
Not too different from your current life.

213
00:15:11,390 --> 00:15:12,550
That's true, in a sense.

214
00:15:13,100 --> 00:15:16,550
I'd just be taking orders from a different person.

215
00:15:16,550 --> 00:15:20,560
But I'd rather die than listen
to someone I don't even like.

216
00:15:21,100 --> 00:15:22,970
Strong words.

217
00:15:22,970 --> 00:15:25,810
Well, at this point, all you
can move is your mouth.

218
00:15:25,810 --> 00:15:28,550
I can move both hands and my left leg.

219
00:15:28,550 --> 00:15:29,820
That's nice.

220
00:15:30,190 --> 00:15:32,930
Anyway, ready for me to take control?

221
00:15:32,930 --> 00:15:35,340
I can't let you die.

222
00:15:35,340 --> 00:15:36,450
Once I put this in you...

223
00:15:36,450 --> 00:15:40,690
When I fight, I always carry two antennae.

224
00:15:40,690 --> 00:15:42,460
For just this kind of situation.

225
00:15:43,490 --> 00:15:45,460
First come, first served.

226
00:15:46,410 --> 00:15:47,710
He stuck it in himself!

227
00:15:48,120 --> 00:15:50,720
Autopilot on.

228
00:15:54,900 --> 00:15:57,260
S-So much aura...

229
00:15:58,130 --> 00:16:00,600
Enemy identified.

230
00:16:00,960 --> 00:16:02,600
Eliminating now.

231
00:16:03,000 --> 00:16:04,250
Go, Pell!

232
00:16:04,250 --> 00:16:06,660
Aim for his leg! Remove the antenna!

233
00:16:18,130 --> 00:16:19,950
Mission complete.

234
00:16:19,950 --> 00:16:22,120
Autopilot disengaging.

235
00:16:22,700 --> 00:16:24,260
Powering off.

236
00:16:28,440 --> 00:16:29,570
Ow...

237
00:16:29,570 --> 00:16:31,420
I already feel it...

238
00:16:31,420 --> 00:16:35,170
I'll be down with muscle aches
for two or three days.

239
00:16:35,880 --> 00:16:38,720
That's why I hate using this!

240
00:16:39,150 --> 00:16:43,140
It makes me stronger, but there's a hefty price.

241
00:16:43,670 --> 00:16:45,750
And I remember nothing that happened,

242
00:16:45,750 --> 00:16:48,110
so I don't feel like I've accomplished anything.

243
00:16:52,200 --> 00:16:55,410
You have considerable power for a lady.

244
00:16:55,710 --> 00:16:58,910
Where was she hiding that vacuum cleaner?

245
00:17:01,050 --> 00:17:02,820
His thread is strong.

246
00:17:02,820 --> 00:17:05,370
If I get caught in it, I won't be able to escape.

247
00:17:09,010 --> 00:17:10,810
Where's the Queen?

248
00:17:11,780 --> 00:17:13,050
Rejoice.

249
00:17:13,050 --> 00:17:14,560
She stands before you now.

250
00:17:15,210 --> 00:17:17,010
That's a lame joke.

251
00:17:17,880 --> 00:17:19,680
Huh? A joke?

252
00:17:20,460 --> 00:17:24,060
You have no manners, brat.
This warrants a hefty punishment.

253
00:17:24,060 --> 00:17:26,630
They are but a beast's ramblings.

254
00:17:26,630 --> 00:17:28,960
Then I'll take you up on that.

255
00:17:28,960 --> 00:17:33,070
When I fight, I always carry two antennae.

256
00:17:34,520 --> 00:17:37,410
It sounds like Feitan found the Queen...

257
00:17:38,170 --> 00:17:40,610
How do I kill her first?

258
00:17:40,610 --> 00:17:42,830
What's this? A child?

259
00:17:43,500 --> 00:17:46,830
Hey, little girl, come over here.

260
00:17:46,830 --> 00:17:48,030
I refuse.

261
00:17:48,490 --> 00:17:49,590
Rejected...

262
00:17:50,090 --> 00:17:52,960
Then I'll come to you.

263
00:17:55,630 --> 00:17:58,300
I'm in a hurry right now.

264
00:18:04,330 --> 00:18:06,230
What's that?

265
00:18:06,880 --> 00:18:08,350
Confetti.

266
00:18:09,750 --> 00:18:11,230
Wind!

267
00:18:18,600 --> 00:18:20,740
That didn't even tickle.

268
00:18:24,880 --> 00:18:28,210
Surrounding me with more paper?

269
00:18:31,090 --> 00:18:33,340
You're wasting your time!

270
00:18:34,080 --> 00:18:34,840
Look.

271
00:18:36,690 --> 00:18:40,010
What? You think that means something?

272
00:18:40,010 --> 00:18:42,260
You really are a stupid kid!

273
00:18:46,350 --> 00:18:47,860
Impossible...

274
00:18:47,860 --> 00:18:50,130
This rope is made of steel!

275
00:18:50,130 --> 00:18:53,570
My fan is made of paper.

276
00:19:07,500 --> 00:19:09,120
Meandering Dance

277
00:19:08,450 --> 00:19:10,120
Meandering Dance.

278
00:19:17,970 --> 00:19:19,130
Look.

279
00:19:21,590 --> 00:19:24,010
Your right arm is next.

280
00:19:26,970 --> 00:19:28,020
An umbrella?

281
00:19:38,430 --> 00:19:40,150
Decent reaction.

282
00:19:41,180 --> 00:19:42,820
A hidden blade?

283
00:19:43,590 --> 00:19:46,160
You like hiding things on you, little boy?

284
00:19:46,590 --> 00:19:48,710
As do you.

285
00:19:48,710 --> 00:19:51,090
When an opponent wears baggy clothing,

286
00:19:51,090 --> 00:19:53,920
it's safe to assume they're hiding something.

287
00:20:17,900 --> 00:20:19,550
What's wrong?

288
00:20:19,550 --> 00:20:21,960
Are you not going to continue your attack?

289
00:20:22,970 --> 00:20:27,870
That is the only way to stop my performance.

290
00:20:34,560 --> 00:20:36,540
You'll pay for this!

291
00:20:36,540 --> 00:20:37,410
Pike...

292
00:20:37,410 --> 00:20:39,610
If I get Pike to use his thread
to tangle up this guy,

293
00:20:39,610 --> 00:20:40,760
he can't make any sound!

294
00:20:41,390 --> 00:20:44,760
Next time, I'll rip you apart!

295
00:20:45,950 --> 00:20:48,390
Your escape is certainly fast...

296
00:20:48,990 --> 00:20:52,600
But not as fast as the speed of sound.

297
00:21:14,000 --> 00:21:16,920
Battle Cantabile...

298
00:21:18,790 --> 00:21:21,280
Jupiter

299
00:21:18,840 --> 00:21:21,260
Jupiter!

300
00:21:39,860 --> 00:21:42,270
Crushed to death.

301
00:21:42,830 --> 00:21:46,410
An appropriate death for a bug.

302
00:21:51,250 --> 00:21:55,360
The Phantom Troupe fight to save their home,

303
00:21:55,360 --> 00:21:57,750
Meteor City, from the Chimera Ants.

304
00:23:25,200 --> 00:23:27,910
Next time: Carnage x And x Devastation.

305
00:23:27,910 --> 00:23:29,330
!aulliK, yalp s'teL

306
00:23:29,330 --> 00:23:30,480
.noG, eurS

307
00:23:30,480 --> 00:23:32,390
What did we just say?

308
00:23:32,390 --> 00:23:34,210
Hint... It was backwards.
